LSF

```json
{
  "application": "LSF",
  "details": {
    "queue": "p1",
    "job_name": "train_mt_04",
    "cores": 16,
    "gpu": "num=1:mode=exclusive_process",
    "walltime": "48:00",
    "memory": "11800MB",
    "output_file": "/dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/jobs/lsf10/logs/R-train_mt_04_%J.out",
    "error_file": "/dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/jobs/lsf10/logs/logs/R-train_mt_04_%J.err",
    "modules": "cuda/12.2",
    "script": "/dtu/p1/johlau/Thesis-Synthex/scripts/classification/train_model.sh"
  }
}
```

This script is designed to run under the LSF (Load Sharing Facility) workload management system. It uses LSF commands to specify resources like CPU cores, a GPU, memory, and wall-time. The script also uses `nvidia-smi` to display information about the GPU and `module load` to load the necessary CUDA module. Finally, it runs the `train_model.sh` script multiple times with different parameters.
